# Microservicos simples com Dapr

## 1) Objetivo
Entregar microservicos simples usando Dapr com pub/sub, state store e observabilidade essencial.

## 2) Estrutura de pastas
```
src/
  Api/
    Controllers/
    Program.cs
  Application/
  Domain/
  Infrastructure/
    Dapr/
    Observability/
dapr/
  components/
deploy/
  docker-compose.yml
  Dockerfile
tests/
  Unit/
  Integration/
```

## 3) Pacotes recomendados
- Dapr.AspNetCore, Dapr.Client
- Serilog.AspNetCore, Serilog.Sinks.Console
- OpenTelemetry.Extensions.Hosting
- OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.AspNetCore, OpenTelemetry.Instrumentation.Http
- OpenTelemetry.Exporter.OpenTelemetryProtocol
- MediatR

## 4) Configuracao (Program.cs)
```csharp
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
builder.Services.AddControllers();
builder.Services.AddDaprClient();
builder.Services.AddMediatR(cfg => cfg.RegisterServicesFromAssemblyContaining<Program>());
builder.Host.UseSerilog((ctx, cfg) => cfg.ReadFrom.Configuration(ctx.Configuration));

builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t.AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation().AddHttpClientInstrumentation())
    .WithMetrics(m => m.AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation());

var app = builder.Build();
app.UseSerilogRequestLogging();
app.MapControllers();
app.MapSubscribeHandler();
app.Run();
```

## 5) Dockerfile (API)
```Dockerfile
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:9.0 AS base
WORKDIR /app

FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:9.0 AS build
WORKDIR /src
COPY . .
RUN dotnet restore ./src/Api/Api.csproj
RUN dotnet publish ./src/Api/Api.csproj -c Release -o /app/publish

FROM base AS final
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/publish .
ENTRYPOINT ["dotnet", "Api.dll"]
```

## 6) docker-compose com Dapr (Kafka pub/sub + Redis state)
```yaml
version: "3.9"
services:
  api:
    build: ..
    environment:
      - ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://+:8080
    ports:
      - "8080:8080"
    depends_on:
      - redis
      - kafka
      - placement

  api-dapr:
    image: "daprio/daprd:1.14"
    command: ["/daprd", "-app-id", "simple-api", "-app-port", "8080", "-placement-host-address", "placement:50005", "-components-path", "/components"]
    volumes:
      - ../dapr/components/:/components
    network_mode: "service:api"
    depends_on:
      - api

  redis:
    image: redis:7-alpine
    ports:
      - "6379:6379"

  zookeeper:
    image: confluentinc/cp-zookeeper:7.4.0
    environment:
      ZOOKEEPER_CLIENT_PORT: 2181

  kafka:
    image: confluentinc/cp-kafka:7.4.0
    depends_on:
      - zookeeper
    environment:
      KAFKA_ZOOKEEPER_CONNECT: zookeeper:2181
      KAFKA_ADVERTISED_LISTENERS: PLAINTEXT://kafka:9092
      KAFKA_OFFSETS_TOPIC_REPLICATION_FACTOR: 1
    ports:
      - "9092:9092"

  placement:
    image: "daprio/placement:1.14"
    command: ["placement", "-port", "50005"]
    ports:
      - "50005:50005"
```

## 7) Componentes Dapr (exemplos)
`dapr/components/pubsub-kafka.yaml`
```yaml
apiVersion: dapr.io/v1alpha1
kind: Component
metadata:
  name: pubsub
spec:
  type: pubsub.kafka
  version: v1
  metadata:
  - name: brokers
    value: kafka:9092
  - name: consumerGroup
    value: simple-api
```

`dapr/components/statestore-redis.yaml`
```yaml
apiVersion: dapr.io/v1alpha1
kind: Component
metadata:
  name: statestore
spec:
  type: state.redis
  version: v1
  metadata:
  - name: redisHost
    value: redis:6379
  - name: redisPassword
    value: ""
```

## 8) Publicacao/assinatura (exemplo minimo)
```csharp
[ApiController]
[Route("events")]
public class EventsController : ControllerBase
{
    private readonly DaprClient _dapr;
    public EventsController(DaprClient dapr) => _dapr = dapr;

    [HttpPost]
    public async Task<IActionResult> Post([FromBody] SimpleEvent evt)
    {
        await _dapr.PublishEventAsync("pubsub", "events.simple", evt);
        return Accepted();
    }
}

[Topic("pubsub", "events.simple")]
public class SimpleEventHandler : IEventHandler<SimpleEvent>
{
    public Task Handle(SimpleEvent evt, CancellationToken ct) => Task.CompletedTask;
}
```

## 9) Observabilidade
- Logs estruturados com traceId e correlation id.
- Traces HTTP e Dapr client; exporter OTLP habilitado.
- Health check simples em `/healthz`.

## 10) Testes
- Unit: handlers MediatR e services.
- Integration: subir docker-compose (redis+kafka+placement) e validar publish/subscribe com Dapr sidecar.

## 11) Checklist
- Dockerfile e docker-compose prontos com sidecar Dapr.
- Componentes Dapr para Kafka e Redis presentes.
- Observabilidade ativa (logs + traces + healthcheck).
- Testes unitarios e de integracao cobrindo publish/subscribe.

## 8) Testes
- Unit: services.
- Integration: endpoints + Dapr sidecar (quando aplicavel).

## 9) Checklist
- Componentes Dapr versionados.
- Observabilidade ativa.
